    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-11T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-11T21:00:00-05:00" n="170"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/229: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-11T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 11, 1935—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>243. From Gibson. My 242, October 11, 11 a.m. In further meeting today Chilean
                    delegation stated Cruchaga has agreed to give his support to the proposal
                    provided it is presented less formally. The chief practical effect of this is
                    that the proposal will not be simultaneously and formally presented in the two
                    capitals.</p>
                <p>The final text of the proposal in the form of a draft treaty was completed this
                    afternoon. I shall not telegraph it unless you so desire.</p>
                <p>Tomorrow is to be devoted to preparing a memorandum explaining the proposal and
                    the reasons for its acceptance. This document to be handed to the two parties
                    and reserved for publication.</p>
                <p>Military Commission has not yet completed its report but early next week the
                    Conference should be able to declare the war at an end. [Gibson.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
